com.streambase.sbunit.ext.matchers
Class FieldBasedTupleMatcher

java.lang.Object
  com.streambase.sbunit.ext.matchers.FieldBasedTupleMatcher
All Implemented Interfaces:
IgnoreNullTransform, TupleMatcher, ValueMatcher
public class FieldBasedTupleMatcher
extends java.lang.Object
implements TupleMatcher, ValueMatcher, IgnoreNullTransform

FieldBasedTupleMatcher matches tuples by comparing their fields against ValueMatchers. It can be used as a ValueMatcher for sub-tuples as well. More complicated behavior can be achieved by calling configuration methods. For example: 

 FieldBasedTupleMatcher m = FieldBasedTupleMatcher.of(t)
          .ignoreNulls()
          .require("name", "Steven")
          .requireNonNull("value");

Warning: FieldBasedTupleMatcher instances are always immutable; a configuration method such as code>ignoreNulls has no effect on the instance it is invoked on.
